        "richtext_AwNbQL": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p><strong>In partnership with the Scottish Book Trust</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_t7PU3Q": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>To celebrate World Book Day, we’re donating mini school packs to five schools across the UK and Northern Ireland. Each pack provides a brilliant new tool to support literacy, whether that’s in the classroom or as part of a listening station in your school library.</p><h4><strong>This is where you come in.</strong></h4><p>We’re inviting you to nominate your school, and the more nominations, the better. Rally together and help us see just how much your school values reading. We’d love to hear about your commitment to literacy, as well as any challenges you’re currently facing.</p><p>It’s simple to take part. Just complete the short form below, and start spreading the word!</p><p></p><p>A panel of Voxblock team members and industry peers (to be confirmed) will review the submissions and select the winners.</p><p>Deadline: 23:59 on 26th March</p><p>Who can apply: Everyone! Whether you’re a teacher, headteacher, or a parent, we’d love to hear from you.</p><p><em>Open to nominations for schools based in the UK and Northern Ireland.</em></p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_Udigpq": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Nominations open on the 5th March",
            "heading_tag": "h3",
            "text_color": "",
            "gradient": ""
